# Security Rules

- NEVER hardcode API keys, secrets, or passwords in any file
- Store secrets in Rails credentials (rails credentials:edit) or ENV vars
- Access via: ENV.fetch('ANTHROPIC_API_KEY') — always use fetch, not []
- Add .env to .gitignore immediately
- Create .env.example with placeholder values
- Rate limit auth endpoints using rack-attack gem
- Scope all queries to the current user:
  current_user.farms.find(params[:id]) NOT Farm.find(params[:id])
- Never trust params[:user_id] — always use current_user.id
- Validate all input server-side with strong parameters AND model validations
- Use parameterized queries always (ActiveRecord handles this — never string interpolate)